# $Id: README,v 8.5 1999/03/06 18:18:11 ksb Exp $

This is the _meta_source_ distribution of the PUCC/ksb install system.
You can change the -DHPUX9 to -Dother-things to compile on other OSs.
This is _NOT_ the original PUCC distribution: ksb modified it to keep
it useful after he left PUCC in 1994.
	
	NEXT2		 -DDEFGROUP=\"wheel\"
	NETBSD		 -DDEFOWNER=\"root\" -DDEFGROUP=\"bin\"
	FREEBSD		 -DDEFOWNER=\"bin\" -DDEFGROUP=\"bin\"
	SUN5		 -DDEFGROUP=\"bin\" -DBSD=43 -DHAVE_QUOTA=0
	SUN4		 -DDEFGROUP=\"bin\"
	SUN3		 -DDEFGROUP=\"bin\"
	EPIX		 -systype bsd43 -DLSARGS=\"-ls\"
	IBMR2		 -DLSARGS=\"-ls\"
	IRIX		 -DLSARGS=\"-ls\" -DDEFGROUP=\"sys\"
	LINUX		 -DDEFGROUP=\"root\"

Look in install.d/configure.h and install.d/install.h for more -Dprop
stuff you can force if you want other values.

If you take the default "binary" group you might have to edit /etc/group
to make it.  This gives you a meaningless group of adornment.
If you like this you'll like "vinst" and "modec" -- soon to come.


N.B.:
	Changes from Greg Becker make installus compile on LINUX.

Bugs:
	installus drops core on SGI (IRIX) I have *no* idea why.
	[I've not have time to look.]  The GNU math library breaks
	as well.  I am giving up on SGI for a while.


